### Phase 3: GraphQL Queries

**3.1 `data-queries/dashboard.graphql`**
```graphql
# label: "Portal Dashboard"
# description: "Dashboard data for logged-in customer"
# $contact_id: {{ request.contact.contact_vid || '' }}
query dashboard($contact_id: String!) {
  CRM {
    contact(uniqueIdentifier: "id", uniqueIdentifierValue: $contact_id) {
      firstname
      lastname
      email
      current_plan
      plan_status
      period_end
      associations {
        p_hair_profile_collection__primary {
          items { onboarding_completed }
        }
        p_order_collection__primary {
          items {
            order_number
            product_name
            status
            total
            estimated_completion
            hs_createdate
          }
          total
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**3.2 `data-queries/orders_list.graphql`** — Contact → all associated orders

**3.3 `data-queries/order_detail.graphql`** — Single order by `order_number` (dynamic slug) + status history

**3.4 `data-queries/hair_profile.graphql`** — Contact → associated Hair Profile with all fields

**3.5 `data-queries/customization_templates.graphql`** — Contact → associated templates

**3.6 `data-queries/invoices.graphql`** — Contact → associated invoices with order links

**3.7 `data-queries/billing.graphql`** — Contact plan properties + HubDB subscription_plans table

**3.8 `data-queries/products.graphql`** — HubDB products table (no contact scoping needed)

**3.9 `data-queries/locations.graphql`** — HubDB affiliated_locations table

**3.10 `data-queries/settings.graphql`** — Contact properties for profile/notification editing

### Phase 4: Templates & Modules Build

**4.1 Portal Layout** (`templates/layouts/portal.html`)
```
Extends base.html. Adds:
- Sidebar (global module: portal-sidebar.module)
- Header bar showing {{ request.contact.firstname }} (global module: portal-header.module)
- {% block portal_content %} for page-specific content
All portal templates extend this layout.
```

**4.2 Build each page template** (dataQueryPath in annotation → corresponding .graphql file):
Each template follows the pattern from the recruiting-agency theme:
```html
<!--
  templateType: page
  isAvailableForNewContent: true
  label: Portal - Dashboard
  dataQueryPath: ../data-queries/dashboard
-->
{% extends './layouts/portal.html' %}
{% block portal_content %}
  {% dnd_area 'portal_content' %}
    {% dnd_section %}
      {% dnd_module path='../modules/dashboard-stats.module' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
      {% dnd_module path='../modules/production-alert.module' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
      {% dnd_module path='../modules/recent-orders.module' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
      {% dnd_module path='../modules/quick-actions.module' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_section %}
  {% end_dnd_area %}
{% endblock %}
```

**4.3 Build each module** (each `.module/` directory contains):
- `meta.json` — label, host_template_types, optional `data_query_path`
- `fields.json` — editable fields (heading text, column count, button text, style options)
- `module.html` — HubL template accessing `data_query.data.CRM.*` or `data_query.data.HUBDB.*`
- `module.css` — Scoped styles

**4.4 System templates** — Brand the membership login/register/reset pages with your styling

### Phase 5: Forms (All Write Operations)

| Form | Purpose | Creates/Updates |
|---|---|---|
| Hair Profile Form | Multi-step: measurements → preferences → lifestyle → photos | Creates/updates Hair Profile custom object + associates to contact |
| New Customization Template | Base type, color, density, method, notes | Creates Customization Template custom object |
| New Support Ticket | Subject, category, priority, description | Creates Service Hub Ticket |
| Profile Update | Name, phone, shipping address | Updates Contact properties |
| Plan Change Request | Plan selection + notes | Updates Contact plan properties (or triggers workflow) |
| Notification Preferences | Checkbox toggles | Updates Contact notification properties |

All forms are HubSpot forms created in the HubSpot UI, embedded in modules via `{% form form_to_use='...' %}`.

### Phase 6: Memberships & Access Control

| Step | Action |
|---|---|
| 6.1 | Create Access Group "Portal Customers" (Content → Memberships) — dynamic list based on contact property `is_portal_customer = true` |
| 6.2 | Gate all `/portal/*` pages behind this access group |
| 6.3 | Assign membership login/register/reset templates to the system pages |
| 6.4 | Configure password requirements and admin email |

### Phase 7: Support & Knowledge Base (Native)

| Step | Action |
|---|---|
| 7.1 | Set up Knowledge Base (Service Hub) — create categories: Care Guides, How-To, Product Info, FAQ |
| 7.2 | Migrate Notion articles → HubSpot KB articles |
| 7.3 | Enable Customer Portal in Service Hub — native ticket view/creation for logged-in contacts |
| 7.4 | Gate KB + Customer Portal behind the same membership access group |

### Phase 8: Deployment & Page Creation

| Step | Action |
|---|---|
| 8.1 | Upload theme: `hs cms upload src hair-solutions-portal` (or legacy `hs upload` — see `scripts/portal_task_complete.sh`) |
| 8.2 | Create pages in HubSpot using your templates: |
| | `/portal` → Portal Dashboard template |
| | `/portal/orders` → Portal Orders template |
| | `/portal/orders/[dynamic]` → Portal Order Detail template (dynamic page, data source: Order) |
| | `/portal/profile` → Portal Profile template |
| | `/portal/customization` → Portal Customization template |
| | `/portal/shop` → Portal Shop template |
| | `/portal/billing` → Portal Billing template |
| | `/portal/invoices` → Portal Invoices template |
| | `/portal/locations` → Portal Locations template |
| | `/portal/settings` → Portal Settings template |
| 8.3 | Gate each page behind the Portal Customers access group |
| 8.4 | Publish all pages |

### Build Order (Recommended Sequence)

```
Week 1: Phase 0 (setup) + Phase 1 (schemas + HubDB tables) + Phase 6 (memberships)
Week 2: Phase 2 (theme scaffold) + Phase 3 (all GraphQL queries) + base layout
Week 3: Phase 4 (templates + modules — dashboard, orders, order detail, profile)
Week 4: Phase 4 cont'd (customization, shop, billing, invoices, locations, settings)
Week 5: Phase 5 (forms) + Phase 7 (KB + support) + Phase 8 (deploy + QA)
```

